sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User (Browser)
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant Kubelet as OpenShift Kubelet
    participant Quay as quay.io/modh<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Ingress as HTTPRoute / Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Sidecar
    participant Workbench as Workbench Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Workbench: Flow 1: Workbench Image Selection and Launch

    User->>Dashboard: Select workbench type<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth2/OIDC
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: List ImageStreams<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Available images<br/>(annotations: image-name, software, python-deps)
    Dashboard-->>User: Display workbench options<br/>(N through N-5 versions)

    User->>Dashboard: Create workbench<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth2/OIDC
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Notebook CR event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet + Service<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    Note over Controller: Injects kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>(RHOAI 3.x) or oauth-proxy (2.x)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute/Route<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA Token
    K8sAPI->>Kubelet: Schedule pod
    Kubelet->>Quay: Pull image<br/>HTTPS/443, Pull Secret
    Quay-->>Kubelet: Container image<br/>(SHA256 digest)
    Kubelet-->>K8sAPI: Pod Running

    User->>Ingress: Access workbench<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Ingress->>RBACProxy: Forward request<br/>TLS terminated
    RBACProxy->>RBACProxy: Authenticate user<br/>(OpenShift OAuth)
    RBACProxy->>Workbench: Forward to JupyterLab<br/>HTTP/8888, plaintext
    Workbench-->>RBACProxy: Response
    RBACProxy-->>Ingress: Authenticated response
    Ingress-->>User: Workbench UI

    Note over User,Workbench: Flow 2: Konflux Image Build (PR)

    participant Dev as Developer
    participant GitHub as GitHub
    participant PaC as Pipelines-as-Code
    participant Tekton as Tekton PipelineRun

    Dev->>GitHub: Open Pull Request<br/>HTTPS/443, GitHub Token
    GitHub->>PaC: Webhook event
    PaC->>Tekton: Trigger PipelineRun<br/>(CEL: pathChanged filter)
    Note over Tekton: git-clone → buildah → SBOM → image-index
    Tekton->>Quay: Push multi-arch image<br/>HTTPS/443, Push Secret
    Tekton->>Tekton: Generate SBOM<br/>& attach attestation
    Tekton-->>GitHub: Report status
